<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10275940>
    dc:description "FIGURES 38–41. Neobisium (N.) sardoum Beier, 1956, position of trichobothria on chelal fingers. 38, male, Grotta del Portello (Urzulei, Sardinia); 39, male, Grotta Su Conti (Urzulei, Sardinia); 40, female, same; 41, female, Grotta Su Colostrargiu (Urzulei, Sardinia)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10275940/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10275954>
    dc:description "FIGURES 62–63. Neobisium (N.) leolatellai n. sp. tritonymph paratype, Grotta della Cava, 17.VII.2010 (Bassiano, Latium). 62, epistome of carapace and right ocular area; 63, id., fixed finger apices of right chela (left) with abnormal position of trichobotrium it and of left chela (right) with normal position of it." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10275954/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10275966>
    dc:description "FIGURES 111–117. Neobisium (N.) zoiai Gardini & Rizzerio, 1986, male, Garb del Dighea, 7.VIII.1994 (Caprauna, Piedmont). 111, anterior margin of carapace and epistome of another male, same data; 112, right chelicera, dorsal view; 113, anterior processes of right coxa I; 114, trochanter, femur and patella of right pedipalp, dorsal view; 115, right pedipalpal chela, dorsal view; 116, same, antiaxial view, with magnified details of teeth at level of trichobothria t and sb; 117, right leg IV, antiaxial view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10275966/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

